newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soymeal ends up on delivery ideas, exports.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soymeal ends up on delivery ideas, exports.

text.p: CBOT soymeal futures closed higher on ideas for light deliveries on the December contract, traders said.
Friday is first notice day for deliveries on the December and there are signs that no soymeal will be posted for delivery.
There also was talk that China this week was seeking U.S. soymeal, they said.
Soyoil closed lower in nearby months but was firm in the deferred contracts. Nearbys were pressed by ideas for heavy delivery notices Friday for soyoil.
Soymeal futures volume was estimated at 13,000 contracts, below the 22,650 traded Tuesday, according to the CBOT.
Soyoil futures volume was estimated at 15,000 contracts, below the 26,737 traded Tuesday.
Soymeal closed $1.10 per ton higher to $2.50 lower, with December up $1.10 at $238.60. Soyoil was 0.08 cent per lb lower to 0.15 higher, with December down 0.08 at 23.23.
